title: Missing Indiana teen found safe after Amber Alert
text:
Missing Indiana teen found safe after Amber Alert Holly V. Hays , holly.hays@indystar.com Published 4:46 p.m. ET Feb. 14, 2017 | Updated 37 minutes ago Chastinea Reeves (Photo: Indiana State Police via Fox59) 16 CONNECT COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The statewide Amber Alert issued Monday for a missing Gary teen has been canceled, according to Gary police. 
The alert for 15-year-old Chastinea Reeves was issued just after 5:30 p.m. Monday, according to a news release. She was found safely in Gary just after 2:30 p.m. Tuesday, according to Lt. Dawn Westerfield, public information officer for the Gary Police Department. 
Reeves had last been seen sometime Monday and was believed to be in extreme danger, according to police. 
Westerfield declined to specify what those circumstances might have been.
